Neiman Marcus Group, Inc. Key Developments

Neiman Marcus Group, Inc. Presents at NRF Protect 2017 Loss Prevention Conference & EXPO, Jun-26-2017
Jun 26 17
Neiman Marcus Group, Inc. Presents at NRF Protect 2017 Loss Prevention Conference & EXPO, Jun-26-2017 . Venue: Gaylord National Harbor Hotel, Washington, United States.


Neiman Marcus Merger Talks Terminated
Jun 14 17
Neiman Marcus Group, Inc. has confirmed that the merger talks with Canadian retailer Hudson's Bay Company (TSX:HSC) have terminated, as its third quarter net loss widened to $24.9 million. In March, the upscale department store retailer said it was exploring "strategic alternatives", including the possibility of a sale, on the back of falling revenues and earnings in its second-quarter. The news of the end of talks came as Neiman Marcus booked net losses of $24.9 million for the three months to April 29, 2017, compared to a loss of $3.8 million last year.


Neiman Marcus Ends Negotiations For A Sale
Jun 13 17
Neiman Marcus Group, Inc. has ended negotiations for a sale, the company said on June 13, 207. In the company’s third quarter earnings conference call, Karen Katz, Chief Executive Officer of Neiman Marcus Group said, “any conversations regarding a partial or full sale of the company have terminated." Though talks of selling the company have ended, Neiman’s could use its intellectual property and real estate to raise more cash. According to a report by market and finance publication Debtwire, the company is considering selling the iconic Neiman Marcus name, as well as its other brand names, including Bergdorf Goodman and MyTheresa, to international buyers.


