Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2017. 

Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC Key Developments

Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended April 29, 2017; Provides Capital Expenditure Guidance for the Fiscal Year 2017
Jun 13 17
Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended April 29, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenues of $1,111,435,000 compared to $1,169,292,000 a year ago. Operating earnings were $38,272,000 compared to $79,673,000 a year ago. Loss before income taxes was $35,446,000 compared to earnings before income taxes of $6,998,000 a year ago. Net loss was $24,874,000 compared to net earnings of $3,790,000 a year ago. Capital expenditures were $47.5 million compared to $78.2 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $135.9 million compared to $173.2 million a year ago.

 
For the nine months period, the company reported revenues of $3,586,118,000 compared to $3,821,149,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $56,800,000 compared to operating earnings of $219,508,000 a year ago. Loss before income taxes was $276,798,000 compared to earnings before income taxes of $3,653,000 a year ago. Net loss was $165,456,000 compared to net earnings of $1,136,000 a year ago. Capital expenditures were $161.5 million compared to $232.0 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $385.6 million compared to $520.4 million a year ago.

For fiscal 2017, the company currently expect capital expenditures on a gross basis to be in the range of $210 million to $220 million and on a net basis, approximately $165 million to $175 million.


Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC to Report Q3, 2017 Operating Results on Jun 13, 2017
May 31 17
Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC announced that they will report Q3, 2017 operating results on Jun 13, 2017


Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC, Q3 2017 Earnings Call, Jun 13, 2017
May 31 17
Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC, Q3 2017 Earnings Call, Jun 13, 2017


